What is Medical Certification of Cause of Death (MCCoD)-
MCCoD is the assignment of a cause of death by an authorised medically trained clinician who fully understands the clinical sequelae of disease or injury that led to death.

MCCoD provides a cause of death statement: cause-of-death statement consists of the wording written in the format used on a death certificate to indicate the cause(s) of death and other significant conditions that contributed to death.

\section*{Definition of terms}

\section*{What is cause of death?}

Cause of death refers to all those diseases, morbid conditions or injuries which either resulted in or contributed to death and circumstances surrounding them.

Causes of death is defined as "all those diseases, morbid conditions or injuries which eitherresulted in or contributed to death and the circumstances of the accident or violence which produced any such injuries".

Definition of cause of death does not include symptoms, Signs and modes of dying such as cardiorespiratory arrest and respiratory failure.

Several underlying causes can be attributed to death but only one underlying cause should be identified and written in the death certificate.

Selection of the underlying cause of death is based on the principles of preventing the primary or underlying cause of death had there been effective preventive programs.

Certification of cause of death refers to assignment of a cause of death by an authorisedmedically trained clinician who fully understands the clinical sequence of conditions.

Death certificate is an official legal document and vital record signed by an authorised Registrarof Births and Deaths that includes cause of death and deceased person's demographics as later entered in an official register of death

The immediate cause of death is the final disease, injury, or complication that directly caused death.

The antecedent or intermediary cause of death is the condition(s) that led to or precipitated the immediate cause of death but occurs at the time between underlying cause of death and immediate cause of death.

The underlying cause of death is the disease or injury (or poisoning) that initiated the chain of events that led directly and inevitably to death.

Underlying Cause of death can also be defined as;
The disease or injury which initiated the train of morbid events leading directly to death, or The circumstances of the accident or violence which produced the fatal injury".

